  "texts": [
    "ConclusionThe investigation highlights the intricacy of identifying prevalent pulmonary conditions, including COVID-19, pneumonia, and lung cancer, emphasizing the critical importance of advanced ML and imaging diagnostic techniques.",
    "The imaging datasets made available to the public underscored the significance of segregating data according to disease specifications because each prominent lung disease has symptoms that specific imaging modalities can detect because of their unique properties.",
    "The research demonstrates the inclination towards X-rays as the prevailing imaging modality, owing to their widespread availability and usage.",
    "CT scans are considered a secondary option, offering improved detail.",
    "ML techniques, particularly CNNs, transfer learning, and ensemble learning, have been crucial in speeding up and enhancing the accuracy of diagnoses."
